The paper discusses the state-of-the-art methods in crowd behavior analysis from a computer vision perspective, which is the primary focus of the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the emergent behavior in physics (complex systems) and biology (animal swarm), which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) and multiagent systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the sample applications of crowd based on attributes and benchmarked datasets, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
